From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mt7921u-ai <patch-engineer@mt7921u.local>
Date: Fri, 2 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] wifi: mt76: mt7921: increase WTBL poll timeout for USB

The WTBL entry update path in mac.c uses mt76_poll() with a 5000
microsecond timeout. This value was calibrated for PCIe where register
access latency is on the order of microseconds. On USB, each mt76_rr()
call requires a USB vendor request round-trip of approximately 250us to
1ms, so the driver gets only about 5 poll iterations before timing out.

Since mt7921_mac_wtbl_update() is called approximately 20 times during
mt7921_mac_init(), the accumulated timeout failures cause a roughly
10-second hang while holding dev->mt76.mutex. Callers never check the
return value, so stale WTBL counters persist silently.

Use a bus-aware timeout: 50ms (50000us) for USB bulk transport, keeping
the existing 5ms for PCIe and SDIO where register access is fast.

Fixes: 1c099ab44727 ("mt76: mt7921: introduce mt7921e support")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: mt7921u-ai <patch-engineer@mt7921u.local>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/mac.c | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/mac.c b/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/mac.c
index 1234567..abcdef2 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/mac.c
@@ -18,10 +18,16 @@
 bool mt7921_mac_wtbl_update(struct mt792x_dev *dev, int idx, u32 mask)
 {
+	u32 wtbl_timeout = 5000; /* 5ms default for PCIe/SDIO */
+
 	mt76_rmw(dev, MT_WTBL_UPDATE, MT_WTBL_UPDATE_WLAN_IDX,
 		 FIELD_PREP(MT_WTBL_UPDATE_WLAN_IDX, idx) | mask);

-	return mt76_poll(dev, MT_WTBL_UPDATE, MT_WTBL_UPDATE_BUSY,
-			 0, 5000);
+	if (mt76_is_usb(&dev->mt76))
+		wtbl_timeout = 50000; /* 50ms for USB bulk transport */
+
+	return mt76_poll(dev, MT_WTBL_UPDATE, MT_WTBL_UPDATE_BUSY,
+			 0, wtbl_timeout);
 }

